HEADWORD: Dulcinea
<hw>Dul*cin"e*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., from
<ets>Dulcinea del Toboso</ets> the mistress of the affections of Don
<er>Quixote</er>.]</ety> <def>A mistress; a sweetheart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I must ever have some <qex>Dulcinea</qex> in my head.</q>
<rj><qau>Sterne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dulciness</ent>⟦br⟧
